This paper deals with the problem of cluster formation and cluster-head selection in Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which is a subfield of computer networking and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses clustering algorithms and their objectives, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of simulation results to compare the performance of different protocols, which involves mathematical analysis and modeling, making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the selection of an optimal solution, which involves information theory and coding, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
